Different groups demanded the resignation of Union HRD Minister Smriti Irani, Union Minister of State for Labour Minister Bandaru Dattatreya and Vice-Chancellor of the Central University of Hyderabad over the death of Dalit scholar Rohith Vemula. The Dalit Samanvaya Samiti and senior writers and activists took out a procession to the Deputy Commissionerâ€™s office and demanded the arrest of Mr. Dattatreya and Vice-Chancellor of varsity P. Appa Rao.They also wanted cases under sections of the SC and ST Atrocities (Prevention) Act to be filed against Ms. IraniEarlier, Dalit Samanvaya Samiti workers burnt the portraits of Prime Minister Narendra Modi, Ms. Irani and Mr. Dattatreya holding them responsible for the death of the Dalit scholar.Meanwhile, students from different colleges staged a protest near the Sardar Vallabhai Patel chowk against the Union government and Mr. Appa Rao.